00:00:01.067 --> 00:00:05.672
Lee:<i> Extraordinary people doing
 extraordinary things.</i>

00:00:08.274 --> 00:00:11.678
<i> By the end of
 a 21-day excavation</i>

00:00:11.678 --> 00:00:15.281
<i> we had discovered the
richest early Hominid site</i>

00:00:15.281 --> 00:00:17.517
<i> ever discovered in the
 history of the planet.</i>

00:00:18.384 --> 00:00:22.755 line:0%
This site is one mile away
from the site of Sterkfontein.

00:00:23.256 --> 00:00:25.290
It's less than
half that distance

00:00:25.290 --> 00:00:27.460
from the second best known site

00:00:27.827 --> 00:00:30.596
in the entire
continent of Africa

00:00:30.596 --> 00:00:34.434 line:0%
the site of Swartkrans,
800 meters away.

00:00:35.101 --> 00:00:36.536 line:0%
It was right under our nose.

00:00:37.170 --> 00:00:40.406
<i> It was an incredible
 environment of science.</i>

00:00:40.406 --> 00:00:42.509
<i>There, we had a fossil tent</i>

00:00:42.509 --> 00:00:45.177
<i>where we kept joking that
 we need a bigger safe</i>

00:00:45.177 --> 00:00:47.146
<i>and we had to buy more boxes</i>

00:00:47.146 --> 00:00:49.015
<i> and more bags than
 we ever envisioned.</i>

00:00:49.015 --> 00:00:53.018
<i> We'd set up a thing to
 find a skeleton</i>

00:00:53.018 --> 00:00:56.322
<i> and we had, first,
 hundreds of remains</i>

00:00:56.322 --> 00:01:00.459
<i>and by the end of it, thousands
 of remains of hominids.</i>

00:01:01.060 --> 00:01:02.962
<i> We would work late
 into the night.</i>

00:01:02.962 --> 00:01:06.632
<i>I, sometimes couldn't get the
scientists out of the cave</i>

00:01:06.632 --> 00:01:10.069
<i> as they excavated for
shifts of six or seven hours</i>

00:01:10.069 --> 00:01:13.139
<i> in these cramped,
 humid conditions.</i>

00:01:13.139 --> 00:01:14.440
And no one could
go get them anyway

00:01:14.440 --> 00:01:16.309
so they could just stay there
as long as they wanted.

00:01:16.309 --> 00:01:17.643
( audience laughter )

00:01:18.811 --> 00:01:23.983
Some people have said, "Well, it
really isn't that dangerous."

00:01:23.983 --> 00:01:26.519
<i>Rick is going to demonstrate
 to you, though that</i>

00:01:26.519 --> 00:01:29.055
<i> just because we
 did not kill anyone</i>

00:01:29.856 --> 00:01:32.892
<i> that this is
 every bit as dangerous</i>

00:01:32.892 --> 00:01:37.063
<i> and extraordinary a risk
as has ever been undertaken.</i>

00:01:37.697 --> 00:01:40.499
<i> These are the easy parts
 you're looking at.</i>

00:01:40.499 --> 00:01:43.769
<i>This was an original thing
we called "Superman Crawl"</i>

00:01:43.769 --> 00:01:45.204
<i> which you go through.</i>

00:01:45.204 --> 00:01:47.040
<i> I can get through that.</i>

00:01:47.440 --> 00:01:50.609
<i> So, that's not a
particularly tight squeeze</i>

00:01:50.609 --> 00:01:53.879
<i> in the scheme of what
 we're doing here.</i>

00:01:53.879 --> 00:01:56.615
<i> For those of you who are
squeamish about closed spaces</i>

00:01:56.615 --> 00:01:59.152
<i> you may look away,
 because it gets worse.</i>

